author: Mary Thurwachter
title: Water-ski team continues to make a splash in Winter Haven
text:
Miss those fabulous Cypress Gardens water-ski shows before Legoland opened in 2011?
You can still see a very good show once a month when the Cypress Gardens Water Ski Team performs on Lake Silver in Winter Haven.
The team, founded in 2012 by former employees of Cypress Gardens, always makes a splash, combining elegance, speed and power.
The audience watches from blankets or lawn chairs they bring themselves and admission is free.
The next show is Aug. 15. Shows begin at 6 p.m. with a pre-show at 5:15 p.m.
For more information, visit www.visitcentralflorida.org .
